author: wn.com
title: Court pushes back arguments as redistricting schedules clash
text: TALLAHASSEE – The Florida Supreme Court issued an order Friday pushing back oral arguments in Florida’s congressional redistricting case to Nov. 10. The court originally scheduled them for Nov. 2, but the Legislature will still be in the middle of a special session to redraw 40 state Senate districts.... ...
